<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="383" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6315: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-24T13:00:00+08:00">May 24, 1933—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 24—3 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>482. Mr. S. G. Cheng, confidential aide to Huang Fu, called this morning
                            and informed me that a preliminary arrangement had been arrived at
                            between Japanese and Chinese military for a cessation of hostilities
                            beginning last night; that this was to be followed by discussions
                            between delegates duly appointed by the Japanese and Chinese military
                            for final arrangements.</p>
                        <p>Repeated Tokyo.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
